FBIS4-61742 "drsov090_b_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-090 Daily Report 7 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Edict Seeks To Control New Oil Companies Yeltsin Edict Seeks To Control New Oil Companies PM0905104994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 7 May 94 Single Edition p 5 PM0905104994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [Russian Federation Presidential Edict No. 845, signed by President Yeltsin and dated 29 April 1994: "On the Retention of State Ownership of Oil Company Shares"] [Text] With a view to ensuring effective state control over the activities of the newly established oil companies, I decree that: The Russian Federation Government shall stipulate during the establishment of the Siberia and Far East Oil Company and the Eastern Oil Company that federal ownership of 51 percent of these companies' shares shall be retained for three years. [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin Moscow, the Kremlin 29 April 1994 No. 845
